articles.author: BILL BARROW
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — A presidential campaign that has careened through a felony trial, an incumbent president being pushed off the ticket and multiple assassination attempts comes down to a final push across a handful of states on the eve of Election Day.
articles.title: Harris and Trump will both make a furious last-day push before Election Day

articles.author: CHRIS MEGERIAN
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — It's the election that no one could have foreseen. Not so long ago, Donald Trump was marinating in self-pity at Mar-a-Lago after being impeached twice and voted out of the White House.
articles.title: A presidential campaign unlike any other ends on Tuesday. Here's how we got here

articles.author: MATT BROWN and FREIDA FRISARO
articles.description: MIAMI (AP) — Concerts and carnivals hosted at polling precincts. “Souls to the Polls” mobilizations after Sunday service. And star-studded rallies featuring Hollywood actors, business leaders, musical artists and activists.
articles.title: Harris, Obamas and voting rights leaders work to turn out Black voters in run-up to Election Day

articles.author: JILL COLVIN and JONATHAN J. COOPER
articles.description: GASTONIA, N.C. (AP) — Donald Trump says he will be the “protector” of women, whether they like it or not.
articles.title: Trump wants to narrow his deficit with women but he's not changing how he talks about them

articles.author: STEVE PEOPLES
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Election Day is nearly upon us. In a matter of hours, the final votes in the 2024 presidential election will be cast.In a deeply divided nation, the election is a true toss-up between Democrat Kamala Harris and Republican Donald Trump.
articles.title: Here's what to watch as Election Day approaches in the U.S.

articles.author: HILLEL ITALIE
articles.description: Quincy Jones, the multi-talented music titan whose vast legacy ranged from producing Michael Jackson's historic "Thriller" album to writing prize-winning film and television scores and collaborating with Frank Sinatra, Ray Charles and hundreds of other recording artists, has died at 91.
articles.title: Quincy Jones, music titan who worked with everyone from Frank Sinatra to Michael Jackson, dies at 91

articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.description: Israel said Monday it had terminated the agreement facilitating the work of the U.N. agency for Palestinian refugees, the main aid provider in Gaza, in what appeared to be a step to implement legislation passed last month that would sever ties with the agency and prevent it from operating in Israel.
articles.title: Middle East latest: Israel ends agreement with UN agency providing aid in Gaza

articles.author: BISWAJEET BANERJEE
articles.description: LUCKNOW, India (AP) — A poorly maintained and overcrowded bus veered off the road and plunged into a deep gorge in northern India on Monday, killing at least 36 people and injuring several others, officials said.
articles.title: At least 36 dead after overcrowded and dilapidated bus skids into a deep gorge in northern India

articles.author: ILLIA NOVIKOV
articles.description: KYIV, Ukraine (AP) — Germany’s top diplomat arrived Monday in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv on an unannounced visit, in what appeared to be a show of European support for Ukraine on the eve of a U.S. presidential election that could bring far-reaching changes in Washington’s policy toward Russia’s all-out invasion of its neighbor.
articles.title: Germany's top diplomat in Kyiv as Ukraine girds for impact of US election on the war

articles.author: DAVID KOENIG
articles.description: Unionized factory workers at Boeing are voting Monday whether to accept a contract offer or to continue their strike, which has lasted more than seven weeks and shut down production of most Boeing passenger planes.
articles.title: Boeing machinists are holding a contract vote that could end their 7-week strike
